{
  "query": "How does drill seeding compare with hydroseeding for establishing sown species in the USA?",
  "relevant_summary": "Based on evidence from USA studies, drill seeding and hydroseeding show different effectiveness patterns for establishing sown species. For drill seeding, results are mixed - one study found increased density of two sown grass species versus hand seeding, but two other studies found drill seeding led to no change or reduced abundance of sown plants compared to hydroseeding or hand seeding. One study found hydroseeding increased abundance of 50% of sown plant species compared to drill seeding in direct comparison. The evidence suggests hydroseeding may be more effective than drill seeding for establishing sown species, showing increased abundance for half of sown species while drill seeding showed more variable results with several studies finding no change or reduced sown plant abundance.",
  "action_ids": [
    "3410",
