  "query": "How do different mechanical seeding methods like drill seeding, strip seeding, and hydroseeding compare in their effects on grassland vegetation in the US and UK?",
  "relevant_summary": "Based on available evidence, different mechanical seeding methods show varying effects on grassland vegetation in the US and UK. Drill seeding (studied in the USA) showed mixed results: three of four studies found no change or reduction in sown plant abundance compared to hydroseeding or hand seeding, though one study found increased density of two sown grass species and increased warm-season grass abundance. Strip seeding (studied in the UK) increased both grass and forb species richness in one study, but a review found that strip seeding resulted in failed introductions of sown species in the majority of cases. Hydroseeding (studied in Spain, USA, and Italy) showed more positive outcomes: one USA study found increased abundance of half of sown plant species compared to drill seeding, one Spanish study found increased overall plant cover in most cases, and an Italian study found increased herb species height, though results for plant species richness were mixed. The evidence base is limited, with most studies coming from the USA for drill seeding and UK for strip seeding, while hydroseeding studies span multiple countries.",
