{
  "query": "How do the outcomes of post-seeding grazing by livestock vary between studies in Europe and the USA?",
  "relevant_summary": "From the evidence found in action document 3423, there were clear differences between European and USA studies. Seven studies examined post-seeding grazing with livestock, with five conducted in Europe (Italy, UK, Hungary) and one in the USA. In Europe, one study in Italy found that grazing after sowing increased plant species richness compared to sowing without grazing, while a UK study found grazing reduced plant richness compared to cutting. A UK study found cattle grazing increased sown species richness more than sheep grazing. In Hungary, livestock grazing after seeding did not alter target plant species cover compared to no grazing. In contrast, the USA study found cattle grazing after seeding increased native plant species richness compared to no grazing but reduced native plant species cover.",
  "action_ids": [
    "3423"
  ]
}

