{
  "query": "What does the evidence from different continents suggest about how sowing different seed types\u2014such as just grasses versus mixed grass and forbs\u2014affects forb abundance?",
  "relevant_summary": "The evidence from different continents shows clear differences in how grass-only versus mixed grass and forb sowing affects forb abundance. Across 50 studies from Europe, North America, and New Zealand, sowing native grass and forb seeds together consistently increased forb abundance, with three of four replicated studies finding increased forb cover or density when both grasses and forbs were sown together. In contrast, when only grass seeds were sown, evidence from 13 studies across North America, Europe, Canada, and South Africa showed that grass-only sowing reduced native forb abundance in one study and showed no change in forb density in another study. The comparison demonstrates that mixed grass and forb sowing is significantly more effective at establishing forb abundance than grass-only sowing across multiple continents.",
